http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Kochi/Nod-for-interim-relief-for-FACT/article14010019.ece

The Board of Directors of Fertilizers and Chemicals Travancore, which met in New Delhi on Tuesday, ratified the agreement to be signed between the Union Ministry of Finance and the fertilizer company for release of the Rs. 1,000-crore interim relief.Formalities for the release of the money had to be completed by January 27 and the company is in time, said sources in the fertilizer company after the Board meeting. The agreement has now been sent to the Finance Ministry, sources added. However, they did not confirm the interest rate at which the money would come. But it is learnt that it would be in the vicinity of the rate at which government securities come.